      <div class="card-tag">FW</div>
    </div>
    <div class="card-body">
      Flow rack slot can add more cases front-to-back <strong>AND</strong> stack cases higher. Highest impact — improves both lane depth and vertical utilization.
      <br><span class="formula">CASES_PER_LANE > CASECAP AND MAX_STACK_LAYERS >= 2</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="card fw-stack">
    <div class="card-header">
      <div class="color-dot"></div>
      <div class="card-title">FW - DoubleStack</div>
      <div class="card-tag">FW</div>
    </div>
    <div class="card-body">
      Flow rack slot can stack cases higher but depth is already maximized. Vertical space is available above current product.
      <br><span class="formula">MAX_STACK_LAYERS >= 2 (depth already at capacity)</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="card fw-depth">
    <div class="card-header">
      <div class="color-dot"></div>
      <div class="card-title">FW - Depth Underutilized</div>
      <div class="card-tag">FW</div>
    </div>
    <div class="card-body">
      Flow rack slot can fit more cases front-to-back but cannot stack higher. Lane has unused depth behind current cases.
      <br><span class="formula">CASES_PER_LANE > CASECAP (no vertical opportunity)</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="card sf-under">
    <div class="card-header">
      <div class="color-dot"></div>
      <div class="card-title">SF - Underutilized Capacity</div>
      <div class="card-tag">SF</div>
    </div>
    <div class="card-body">
      Static shelf slot can hold more cases based on shelf footprint (24" × facing width × 12") and product dimensions.
      <br><span class="formula">FLOOR(24/Max) × FLOOR(FacingWidth/Med) × FLOOR(12/Min) > CASECAP</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="card ok">
